# Colors [![Latest](https://img.shields.io/github/release/heitorpolidoro/colors.svg?label=latest)](https://github.com/heitorpolidoro/colors/releases/latest)
Set of constants to simplify print with colors

#### How to use:
```
from colors import *
print(Red, 'Error')
```
<span style='color:red'>Error</span>

The package creates a wrapper in the default `print` to remove the color 
on every print. So you don't have to worry to put the `Color_Off`.  
```
print('This is ', Green, 'Green.')
print('This is not.')
```
This is <span style='color:green'>Green.</span><br>
This is not.

Unless you really wanted to
```
print(Blue, 'Color on', Color_Off, ' Color off')
```
<span style='color:blue'>Color on</span> Color off

**SIDE EFFECTS**

The wrapper removes single spaces strings (`" "`) so this:
```
print('Hello', 'World')
```
Will print: `HelloWorld` instead of `Hello World`.


